This paper deals with deep learning-based methods for correspondence between objects of different semantic categories. The paper specifically mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and sparse correspondence, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also mentions the use of semantic relationships between parts of objects, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper deals with the matching of objects, which is a topic in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
